The game was positively received by the reviewer of ''[[Your Commodore]]'' who gave it a score of 4/5, saying that it was "among my top five favourites".  Although the graphics were not "totally first class" the game was said to be "amazing."<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://archive.org/stream/02-your-commodore-magazine/Your_Commodore_Issue_02_1984_Nov#page/n31/mode/2up|title = Your Commodore Magazine Issue 02|date = November 1984}}</ref>

In the first issue of ''[[Zzap!64]]'' the game was placed 21st in a list of the top 64 games list.<ref name="Retro"/> ''Zzap!64''  also favourably reviewed a budget re-release of ''Forbidden Forest''.  Although noting that the graphics were blocky they praised the game's atmosphere, soundtrack and gameplay.  It was given an overall score of 82%.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.zzap64.co.uk/cgi-bin/displaypage.pl?issue=030&amp;page=110&amp;thumbstart=0&amp;magazine=zzap&amp;check=1|title = Impossible to Display Scan}}</ref>

